1 Xml file contains 1 transmission. Below are some simple tables that will explain the structure of the file. To avoid a gigantic, nested mess the file structure has been split into its individual components.

Lines can either be a "child" of the "message" element or of the order that they belong to. This option is provided because it can be easier to translate files with a non-nested structure to EDI formats.
A node in an XML file can be of type "container" (it contains other elements) or "data" (it contains data). 1 Our xml structure attempts to avoid using xml attributes.

The minimum and maximum number of times this element will appear within this structure. 0/1 means it can appear a minimum of 0 (i.e. the element could be absent) and a maximum of 1 time. 1/99 means it can appear between 1 and 99 times. 1/inf means the element can appear between 1 and "infinite" times. Infinite in the sense that it has no upper bound.

By default the lines on the invoice are listed separately to the orders, we can, if needed, "nest" the lines within the orders so that each order "contains" its lines. Default Behaviour Below is a "toy" example of the default behaviour.

On request, Proper Music can add additional fields to an individual feed. If you would like additional specific data, then please contact your label manager or other Proper Music contact who can request additional fields, for copyright and data protection reasons, not all the data held by Proper Music can be made available in a feed. When you are given the Rich Feed 2.0 connection details, it will connect you to a root folder. Depending on your business relationship with Proper Music, you will then see a maximum of three sub folders:
This folder contains the cost feeds, if applicable for you, this will contain your Proper Music Dealer price and Net price. Available in XML, JSON & CSV format.
This folder contains the product feeds, with description of each product Available in XML & JSON format.

This folder contains the stock feed, which shows the stock available to order from Proper Music. The feeds available vary depending on the destination of the feed, Proper Music will configure the feeds as required. Available in XML, JSON & CSV format.

Each Rich Feed will thew following file types: Full- The weekly full feed of all available products. Inc-new - Containing records that were not in the last feed update. Inc-update - Containing records that have been changed since the last feed update. NB. This does not include products where only the stock level has changed. On the product feed there is an additional file Inc-remove - Containing products that have been removed since the last full feed. Bold now works

The feeds are split into data chunks, to avoid the files being too large to transfer/read. A standard naming convention is used for all files: Position Content Example Start Feed number internal ID remains static for a feed 12 2nd full or inc Identifies if feed is full or incremental inc 3rd Date or Date & Time _Full feed has date in format yymmdd Incremental has date+time in format yymmddhhmmss 230531150620 4th File Data chunk Numeric value 001-999 identifying data chunk {001} Extension File Format .json or .xml or .csv .xml Example: 12-inc-230531150620{001} .xml

Each file has a "header" section which confirms the files content: Field JSON XML Description version String String Feed Version file_name String String File Name\Type weightUnits String String Units used for weights 4dimensionUnits String String Units used for measurements
